First Lady Michelle Obama and former First Lady Laura Bush will be hosting a symposium called "Investing in Our Future" at the U.S.-Africa Leaders Summit. The symposium will bring together African first spouses, leaders from NGOs and non-profits, private sector partners, and other experts to discuss advancements for women and girls in Africa. The panels will focus on investments in education, health, and economic development through public-private partnerships. The symposium will also feature remarks by President George W. Bush about the expansion of the Pink Ribbon Red Ribbon initiative to fight against women's cancers. Throughout the day, organizations will announce commitments to new initiatives and partnerships dedicated to empowering women in Africa. The symposium will conclude with a marketplace and networking reception showcasing organizations and companies supporting women and girls in Africa.